  <h2>Final thoughts</h2>
  <p>
    A practical pantry should make cooking, shopping and daily routines easier. Start by
    removing expired or unused items, then group food by purpose and choose storage that suits
    your actual pantry.
  </p>
  <p>
    Baskets, airtight containers, labels, shelf risers and turntables can all be useful, but
    only when they solve a real problem. Improve one shelf or category at a time, and the
    pantry will become easier to manage without needing a full kitchen redesign.
  </p>

